            "title": "GE Aerospace expected to report Q4 earnings of $1.43 per share, up from $1.32 last year, with revenue estimate of $11.21 billion. Delta Air Lines selects GEnx engines to power 30 new Boeing 787-10s, impacting GE Aerospace stock.",
            "id": "6e0ac694-d632-4009-8bdd-521b277efaaf",
            "description": "GE Aerospace, a NYSE-listed company, is set to unveil its Q4 earnings on Jan. 22. Analysts predict earnings of $1.43 per share, a rise from $1.32 in the same period last year. Revenue forecasts for the quarter stand at $11.21 billion, up from $9.88 billion in the previous year. The company recently announced a deal with Delta Air Lines (NYSE: DAL) for GEnx engines to power 30 new Boeing 787-10s, with an option for 30 more planes, along with spare engines and ongoing service support. Following this news, GE Aerospace's shares surged by 2% to reach $318.50 at the close of trading on Wednesday.",
